models. When we set an evolutionary model motivated prior to the mass of
β Pictoris b, we find a solution in the 10-11 MJup
range. Conversely, β Pictoris c's mass is well constrained, at 7.8
± 0.4 MJup, assuming both planets are on coplanar
orbits. These values depend on the assumptions on the distance of the
β Pictoris system. The absolute astrometry HIPPARCOS-Gaia data are
