± 0.84 Earth masses. This work, along with the previously
published RV papers on the K2-18 planetary system, highlights the importance of understanding the time-sampling and of modelling the simultaneous planet plus stochastic activity, particularly when
searching for sub-Neptune-sized planets with radial velocities.

